<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="132" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1631,2042]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1770,1796]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Remarks.</emphasis>
Examination of a 
<typeStatus box="[522,618,1770,1796]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gusenleitner 2006:" authorityYear="1353" box="[656,856,1770,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Calligaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zetteli">
<emphasis box="[656,856,1770,1796]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Calligaster zetteli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
showed us that this species does not belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="de Saussure" authorityName="de Saussure" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Calligaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Calligaster</emphasis>
de Saussure
</taxonomicName>
but to 
<taxonomicName authority="de Saussure" authorityName="de Saussure" authorityYear="1875" box="[462,754,1804,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Pseudozumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[462,611,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Pseudozumia</emphasis>
de Saussure
</taxonomicName>
and it is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="van der Vecht. The" authorityName="van der Vecht. The" authorityYear="1963" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Pseudozumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[1100,1344,1804,1830]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Pseudozumia gracilis</emphasis>
van der Vecht. The
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[279,375,1840,1866]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">paratype</typeStatus>
is shown in 
<figureCitation box="[517,653,1839,1865]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–13" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1973,1997]" captionTargetBox="[193,1394,1407,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-33@7.[193,1394,1407,1949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 12–13. Pseudozumia gracilis van der Vecht, 1963, ♀ (paratype of Calligaster zetteli Gusenleitner, 2006). 12, Head, frontal view. 13, Mesosoma, dorsal view." pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Figs. 12–13</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1631,2042]" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">
The attribution to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saussure" authorityYear="1875" box="[404,553,1874,1900]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Pseudozumia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[404,553,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Pseudozumia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not to 
<taxonomicName box="[682,808,1874,1900]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Calligaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[682,808,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Calligaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was justified by the following characters [characters of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,277,1908,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Calligaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,277,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="129">Calligaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in brackets]: mandibles elongate [mandibles short], cephalic foveae present [cephalic foveae absent], mid tibia with one spur [mid tibia with two spurs], propodeum with pointed lobes near propodeal valvula [propodeum without pointed lobes], T1 subtriangular with striate elliptical area in the middle [T1 petiolate and parallel sided, striate but without a sharply delimited elliptical area].
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="6" pageNumber="130" startId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[225,1363,181,1920]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1943,2004]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,328,1943,1967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">FIGURES 9–10.</emphasis>
Male genitalia, from left to right: aedeagus in lateral view, aedeagus in ventral view, digitus and volsella. 9, 
<taxonomicName authority="Selis" authorityName="Selis" authorityYear="2022" box="[151,406,1980,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Calligaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ilocana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,348,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">Calligaster ilocana</emphasis>
Selis
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[416,496,1980,2004]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[416,496,1980,2004]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
10, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bequaert, 1940" authorityName="Bequaert" authorityYear="1940" box="[541,919,1980,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Eumenidae" genus="Calligaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsi">
<emphasis box="[541,754,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="130">Calligaster williamsi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bequaert, J." box="[761,919,1980,2004]" pageId="6" pageNumber="130" pagination="124 - 126" refId="ref4132" refString="Bequaert, J. (1940) A new species of Calligaster from the Philippine Islands (Hymenoptera, Vespidae, Subfam. Zethinae). The Pan-Pacific Entomologist, 16, 124 - 126." type="journal article" year="1940">Bequaert, 1940</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
